a.xlink:title: A concept that indicates whether an alphabet represents amino acids.
The generic alphabet concept that covers most data types used in ranges.
The basis for bio::alphabet, but requires only rank interface (not char).
A refinement of bio::semialphabet that adds assignability.
A CRTP-base that makes defining a custom alphabet easier.
This is an empty base class that can be inherited by types that shall model bio::aminoacid_alphabet.
A CRTP-base that refines bio::alphabet_base and is used by the amino acids.
